  "body": "### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nif the size is more than 8KB , content-length header should not be present and transfer-encoding should have value of chunked. if less than 8 KB transfer-encoding should not be present , but content-length should be present. \r\n\r\nThis is cause Nginx to reject the response and clients calling the API receives 502 error.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nif the size is more than 8KB , content-length header should not be present and transfer-encoding should have value of chunked.\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\neven with response size greater than 8 KB content-length header is coming in response header. \r\n\r\n### How to Reproduce?\r\n\r\n1. create a Quakus App with 3.2.2-FINAL version \r\n2. create an Endpoint that returns more than 8 KB data. \r\n3. observer the response header, it has content-length and transfer-encoding is present. \r\n\r\n\r\nFix: \r\nServerSerialisers.class in rest-easy library should be removing content-length header based on this condition. but Since we are not using EqualIgnore case, it's skipping past this step.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"922\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-07-26 at 1 49 01 PM\" src=\"https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/assets/15947082/d433f4f8-ae46-47b9-9824-159d74ee3595\">\r\n\r\n### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`\r\n\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Output of `java -version`\r\n\r\n17\r\n\r\n### GraalVM version (if different from Java)\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Quarkus version or git rev\r\n\r\n3.2.2-FINAL\r\n\r\n### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)\r\n\r\nmaven 3.9.2\r\n\r\n### Additional information\r\n\r\n_No response_",
